  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ZOCS, a local NGO working to help vulnerable children access education is the implementing partner on the access to education and skills training for girls and vulnerable children.  The objective of the project  is to enable vulnerable girls and boys to complete secondary school education and acquire skills in order to live meaningful and productive adult lives.  The project also advocates with government for financial and materials support to community schools attended by the poor and vulnerable.</narrative>
